    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1962-11-09T20:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1962-11-09T20:45:00-05:00" n="512"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d512">
                <head>512. Telegram 1710 from <gloss target="#t_USUN_1">USUN</gloss>, November
                        9<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d512fn1">Report of follow-on conversation
                        between <persName corresp="#p_MJJ_1">McCloy</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_KVV_1">Kuznetsov</persName> based on telephone conversation
                        between <persName corresp="#p_MJJ_1">McCloy</persName> and Gilpatric <gloss
                            target="#t_re_1">re</gloss>
                        <persName corresp="#p_KVV_1">Kuznetsov</persName> allegations that U.S.
                        vessels improperly searched Soviet ships. Confidential. 1 p. <gloss
                            target="#t_USUN_1">USUN</gloss> Files: <gloss target="#t_NYFRC_1"
                            >NYFRC</gloss> 84–84–001, Outgoing Telegrams, 1953–1963.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>New York</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1962-11-09T20:45:00-05:00">November 9, 1962, 8:45 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d512-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d512-1"/>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_EyesOnly_1">Eyes Only</gloss> for Secretary—<gloss
                        target="#t_Dept_1">Dept</gloss> pass White House. REF: 1709. Subject
                    Cuba.</p>
                <p>In accordance telecon <persName corresp="#p_MJJ_1">McCloy</persName>/Gilpatric 6
                    p.m. <persName corresp="#p_MJJ_1">McCloy</persName> immediately called <persName
                        corresp="#p_KVV_1">Kuznetsov</persName> to advise that, while we had been
                    unable obtain complete report <gloss target="#t_re_1">re</gloss> SOV allegations
                    impropriety in procedures used checking some outgoing missile bearing ships,
                    orders outlining agreed procedures had been reconfirmed include no stopping of
                    SOV ships and no opening of hatches.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_MJJ_1">McCloy</persName> advised <persName
                        corresp="#p_KVV_1">Kuznetsov</persName> that interpreter available on USNS
                        <hi rend="italic">Perry</hi> was not well qualified in Russian and that any
                    misunderstanding <gloss target="#t_re_1">re</gloss> opening of hatches probably
                    resulted from poor translation.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_MJJ_1">McCloy</persName> advised <persName
                        corresp="#p_KVV_1">Kuznetsov</persName> that when complete report of
                    incident was received, it would be provided.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_MJJ_1">McCloy</persName> then pointed out that, since some
                    of SOV ships carried different number of missiles than we had been advised, they
                    should be liberal with us as to what ships we observed. <persName
                        corresp="#p_MJJ_1">McCloy</persName> said that one ship, the <hi
                        rend="italic">Labinsk</hi>, was to have carried two missiles and had none
                    and another had one more missile than number furnished us by SOVS. <persName
                        corresp="#p_MJJ_1">McCloy</persName> stated further that we had observed 38
                    of 42 missiles SOVS had reported.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed corresp="#p_SAE_1">
                        <persName corresp="#p_SAE_1">Stevenson</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
